SIMPLE: peaceful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peaceful
<hw>Peace"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Possessing or enjoying peace; not disturbed by war, tumult,
agitation, anxiety, or commotion; quiet; tranquil; <as>as, a
<ex>peaceful</ex> time; a <ex>peaceful</ex> country; a <ex>peaceful</ex>
end.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not disposed or tending to war, tumult or agitation;
pacific; mild; calm; peaceable; <as>as, <ex>peaceful</ex>
words</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Peaceable</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>--<wordforms><wf>Peace"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos>. --
<wf>Peace"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>peacekeeper</ent>⟦br⟧
